page.title: 01Life in Birch Wood,Tiptree
page.content: Birch Wood contains quite a lot of different types of trees including Birch, Oak, Ash, Willow, Beech and Sweet Chestnut. Roughly in the middle of the wood is a reservoir and by that a murky pond. The reservoir is a place where many people fish. The pond next to it contains many newts,even some Great Crested Newts. The bird life on the water is two ducks, eight ducklings, two moorhens and a group of four baby moorhens. Also when we were looking around, that was Nicky, Johnathan,Richard,Peter,Mrs Beal and I.We saw Dragonflies and many plants. In trees were squirrels, and a dray, and a Freshwater Mussel, that was probably taken from the reservoir. We found Woodpecker holes without Woodpeckers. We saw Jay and Owl feathers.They were definately Jays because they had a blue mark.
